Sonographically detected fetal choroid plexus cysts. Frequency and association with aneuploidy. Over a 22-month period, 1045 second-trimester pregnancies were evaluated with ultrasound for the presence of choroid plexus cysts. The frequency of fetal choroid plexus cysts was 3.6% (38/1045). The outcome of the 38 fetuses possessing choroid plexus cysts was as follows: One fetus had triploidy, an occurrence not previously reported one fetus had hydrocephalus and a normal karyotype